e:T5b8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What SOC 2 trust service criteria does Codepliant cover?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant maps your codebase against all five SOC 2 Trust Service Criteria: Security (CC), Availability (A), Processing Integrity (PI), Confidentiality (C), and Privacy (P). Most startups begin with Security, which is the only required category."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Codepliant replace a SOC 2 audit?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. SOC 2 requires an independent auditor. Codepliant accelerates your preparation by generating evidence documentation, identifying control gaps, and producing a readiness checklist so you go into the audit well-prepared."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does SOC 2 preparation usually take?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Without tooling, SOC 2 Type I preparation typically takes 3-6 months and costs $50,000-$100,000. Codepliant reduces the documentation burden from weeks to minutes by generating control mappings and evidence from your actual code."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Codepliant work with my existing security tools?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant complements your security stack. It scans your code to detect what controls you already have (encryption, access controls, logging, monitoring) and documents them in a format auditors expect."}}]}b:["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"SoftwareApplication\",\"name\":\"Codepliant SOC 2 Compliance Tool\",\"applicationCategory\":\"DeveloperApplication\",\"operatingSystem\":\"macOS, Linux, Windows\",\"description\":\"SOC 2 compliance tool that scans your codebase and generates readiness checklists, control mappings, and evidence documentation.\",\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"Offer\",\"price\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"USD\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"py-20 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[680px] mx-auto","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-accent mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase","children":"SOC 2 Compliance"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"SOC 2 Compliance Tool for Startups"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-muted mb-12","children":"SOC 2 compliance is the gold standard for SaaS security, and enterprise buyers expect it. Codepliant scans your codebase to generate a SOC 2 readiness checklist, map your existing controls to Trust Service Criteria, and produce evidence documentation — cutting months off your audit preparation."}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"What SOC 2 requires from your engineering team"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","CC6 — Logical and physical access controls",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-2","children":"CC6 — Logical and physical access controls"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"Demonstrate how your application controls access to systems and data. Codepliant detects authentication mechanisms, RBAC implementations, and session management in your code."}]]}],["$","div","CC7 — System operations monitoring",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":["$Lf","$L10"]}],"$L11","$L12"]}]]}],"$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18"]}]}]],null,"$L19"]}]
